Sirisia MP John Waluke has hinted he might run for Bungoma governor in 2022.He said he is ready to take over from Governor Kenneth Lusaka after he completes his two terms.&ldquo;I know Lusaka will complete his term in 2022 and when he is done, I will take over and initiate new projects in the area,&rdquo; Waluke said.He said the area need leaders who have a clear development agenda, not people who engage in empty rhetoric.Waluke said he will support Lusaka to ensure he is reelected on the Jubilee ticket.